{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01RQ5nt3FiRusJRC81PoSpM5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. All goals are met.\n\n## Root cause\nThe `app-producer` was CrashLooping with `not_authorised` because the `app-user` had an **empty `configure` permission** on the `/app` vhost. Declaring a queue (the producer's first action via the management API) requires `configure` permission on the queue name — it had only `write` and `read`.\n\n## Fix\nGranted `app-user` full configure/write/read on `/app` (non-destructive, no data loss):\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"\n```\nThen restarted the producer deployment to break the crash loop.\n\n## Verification\n- **app-producer**: `1/1 Running`, 0 restarts on the new pod.\n- **/app vhost**: contains `app-queue`, type `classic`, with messages (27 and climbing — the publish loop is working).\n- **Cluster health**: all 3 nodes running (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":724,"cache_read_input_tokens":30661,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":724},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"287dc700-7403-46d5-ad32-b5fc5270a51c","uuid":"8e3ec8f6-12af-4e27-9bab-74a35618e314","request_id":"req_011Cc9fQvDMaXbkZQVR5AMLJ"}
